Exercises

1. Write a command that prints out the string “hello, world”.
Extra credit: As in Listing 1, do it two different ways,
both with and without using quotation marks.

2. Type the command echo ’hello (with a mismatched single quote),
and then get out of trouble using the technique from Box 4.

Solutions

1.

$ echo "hello, world"
$ echo hello, world

2. $ echo 'hello

//terminal hangs

Ctrl + C

//terminal restarts
